title.narrative: By 2020, policy makers have increased evidence on early learning and school readiness programmes, leveraging advocacy and resources to scale up.

description.narrative: Significant progress has been made in increasing access to early learning and strengthening Early Childhood Education (ECE) system. ECE diagnostic assessment has supported the government in critical reflection of evolving ECE system and in informing the Education Sector Plan (ESP) with concrete actions for building ECE system. The Accelerated School Readiness (ASR) pilot has reached 3,959 children (1,898 girls) in Zambezia. Over 11,000 children aged 3–5 years affected by cyclone Idai and Kenneth benefitted from Early Childhood Development in Emergencies (ECDiE) kits. Furthermore,18 intersectoral materials on holistic ECD were produced and will support operationalization of the nurturing care framework. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/01/2020
